<1ST_LINE>r a AM-TellerShot     10-19 0188</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Teller Shot,0194</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bank Teller Slain During Robbery</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HAMMOND, Ind. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A teller was shot to death during a bank
robbery Tuesday by three men wearing masks and gloves, officials
said.
   The three men, armed with shotguns and pistols, entered the
Mercantile National Bank branch in this Chicago suburb shortly
after 10:30 a.m. The teller was shot in the head and a security
guard was disarmed, said Detective Sgt. Ray Myszak.
   The trio escaped with an undetermined amount of money, Myszak
said.
   The teller was identified as Evelyn Sostaric, 60, of Hammond,
the wife of an investigator for the Lake County prosecutor's office
who is also a retired police officer.
   Mrs. Sostaric was pronounced dead at St. Margaret hospital about
an hour after being shot, said hospital spokeswoman Rose Hand.
   Mercantile Bank Chairman Joseph Morrow offered a $20,000 reward
for information leading to the arrest of the gunman.
   ``This was done to her with no provocation whatsoever,'' Morrow
said of the shooting.
   A witness who had pulled into the bank's drive-up window told
police Mrs. Sostaric had tried to tell her the bank was being
robbed.
</TEXT>
