<HEAD>PLO Parliament To Meet In Early November</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALGIERS, Algeria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Palestine Liberation Organization's
parliament in exile, the Palestine National Council, will meet in
Algiers during the first 10 days of November, a PLO official said
on national television.
   The meeting has been planned for months to discuss the situation
in the occupied territories where Palestinians have been in revolt
since December 1987. News reports have said the council is expected
to formally create a Palestinian state and a government in exile
during the meeting.
   Interviewed by Algerian television Tuesday night, Moundher
Dajani said the council meeting would be held ``between Oct. 31 and
Nov. 10, taking into consideration the fact that a referendum will
be held in Algeria on Nov. 3.''
   Algerians will be voting that day on political changes proposed
by President Chadli Bendjedid following street riots earlier this
month.
   ``The declaration of independence will be adopted,'' Moundher
said. ``The Palestinian state will be created despite the
declarations of (Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhak) Shamir.''
