<HEAD>Police Arrest 19, Seize Illegal Arms</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DAR ES SALAAM, Tanzania (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police arrested 19 people and
recovered 13 illegal firearms after a series of highway robberies,
it was reported Wednesday.
   The arrests and arms seizures took place between Aug. 4 and Oct.
3 in the regions of Dar es Salaam, Kigoma, Mtwara, Mbeya and
Iringa, said police inspector Harun Mahundi, according to the
newspaper reports.
   Gunmen who attacked buses in the regions killed one person,
Mahundi said.
   Mahundi said the arms seized included four submachine guns, four
rifles and 32 rounds of ammunition.
