<HEAD>Tuskegee Mayor Fights, Kills Pit Bulls That Attacked Him</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TUSKEGEE, Ala. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mayor Johnny Ford was attacked by two
stray pit bulldogs while jogging behind his home Wednesday morning
and took refuge in a tree for 2{ hours before a passer-by came to
his aid and shot the dogs with a pistol.
   ``I battled them with my hands and feet by using karate kicks as
best I could to keep them at bay,'' Ford said. ``The dogs were so
vicious they momentarily turned on each other and that gave me time
to get to a tree.''
   Ford said he was bitten on the legs, arms and hands. He was
later treated at a hospital and released.
   ``I'm OK,'' Ford said. ``I'm not bitten up that bad. The most
important thing is they were not rabid.'' He said the dogs were
tested by a local veterinarian after they were killed.
   Ford said after the dogs were shot he beat them with a limb
until they were dead.
