<HEAD>Illinois GOP Brochure Says Criminals Will Vote For Dukakis</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Dukakis</HEAD>
<DATELINE>QUINCY, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Republican brochures denounced Wednesday
by Democratic presidential nominee Michael Dukakis were distributed
by the Illinois GOP.
   One of them bore the headline, ``All the Murderers and Rapists
and Drug Pushers and Child Molesters in Massachusetts Vote for
Michael Dukakis,'' and the second one contained a similar message
but bore a less inflammatory headline, ``Vote for Vice President
George Bush for President.''
   The first brochure alleged that convicts in Massachusetts have
the right to vote.
   It cited Dukakis' opposition to the death penalty and his
support for the controversial Massachusetts prison furlough program.
   The brochure alleged that Dukakis has said that if the death
penalty were reinstituted in Massachusetts by popular vote he would
commute death sentences.
   It said the Massachusetts governor supports allowing convicts to
vote and vetoed a bill to stop letting convicts out of prison on
weekend passes.
   The second brochure cited the Massachusetts furlough program and
specifically the case of Willie Horton, the furloughed convicted
who raped a Maryland woman. It said that convicted Illinois
mass-murderer ``would be eligible for weekend passes''' under the
Massachusetts program.
   The material also touched on Social Security, saying that Bush
would never raid the trust fund as alleged by Dukakis and
contending that the Massachusetts governor ``has taken huge sums of
money from the Massachusetts pension funds to balance the state
budget.''
</TEXT>
