<HEAD>Bomb Threat Turns Out False on Campaign Trail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SIKESTON, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fire officials on Wednesday searched a Head
Start center Wednesday after an unidentified caller claimed a bomb
was planted in a building where Barbara Bush was visiting, police
said.
   No bomb was found in the center on the city's western edge.
   Public safety director Mike Phelan said the bomb threat was made
to a dispatcher for the city's 911 emergency system by a male who
did not identify himself. Sikeston, a city of about 20,000 in
southeastern Missouri, is located 120 miles south of St. Louis.
   ``I think it was just a prank. No bomb was found. She was not
upset whatsoever,'' Phelan said of the incident. ``She handled it
very calmly and very professionally.''
