<2ND_LINE>AM-Connecticut Poll,120</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bush Has 10-Point Lead Over Dukakis In Connecticut, Poll Shows</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Republican George Bush leads Democrat
Michael Dukakis 46 percent to 36 percent in a University of
Connecticut poll released Wednesday.
   The statewide poll, conducted for The Hartford Courant, compares
with a 2-point margin he enjoyed in the last poll taken Sept. 12 to
Sept. 18.
   The latest survey was taken by telephone between Oct. 11 and
Sunday, straddling the final Bush-Dukakis debate Oct. 13, and has a
margin of error of plus or minus five percentage points.
   Conducted by the Institute for Social Inquiry at the University
of Connecticut, the poll is based on responses from 512 people who
are either registered to vote or said they were certain to register.
