<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-Chemicals     10-19 0255</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Chemicals,0264</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dow Reports Record Third Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIDLAND, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dow Chemical Co. said its third-quarter
profit soared 92 percent over last year due to strong sales of
chemicals and consumer and industrial products.
   Net income for the three months ended Sept. 30 was a record $632
million, or $3.36 a share, compared with earnings of $330 million,
or $1.72 a share, in 1987. Sales were $4.15 billion, up 24 percent
from $3.36 billion in the year-earlier period.
   For the first nine months of the year, Dow's profit totaled $1.7
billion, or $9.32 a share, on sales of $12.38 billion. A year ago
it netted $891 million, or $4.64 a share, on sales of $9.78 billion.
   ``All business segments in all geographic areas had strong
performances in what has typically been an off-season quarter,''
said Enrique C. Falla, Dow's financial vice president.
   Dow said its sales were up 26 percent in the United States, 14
percent in Europe and 31 percent in the rest of the world, with
major gains in Canada and the Pacific.
   Caustic soda and ethylene glycol were top contributors to strong
volume increases in the basic chemicals segment, the company said.
   DowBrands' plastic food wrap business and sales of Merrell Dow
Pharmaceuticals Inc.'s probucol cholesterol reducing agent were top
selling consumer specialties, it said.
   The company said strong sales in polycarbonate polymer as result
of expanded production in Texas aided growth in industrial
specialties. Polycarbonate polymer is a strong, plastic-like
substance used in the auto, appliance and other industries.
</TEXT>
