<HEAD>London Shares Close Higher</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES thruout with closing figures.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices rose Wednesday on the London stock
exchange in trading which dealers said was dominated by takeover
speculation.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index rose 5.5
points, or 0.03 percent, to 1862.5. The market opened higher and
the 100-share index went as high as 1867.8.
   At the close, the narrower Financial Times 30-share index was up
3.7 points at 1513.2, while the broader Financial Times 500-share
index rose 3.91 points to 1056.02.
   Volume was relatively healthy by recent standards, as 595.5
million shares changed hands, compared with the 562.8 million
shares traded Tuesday. Much of the volume continued to be
concentrated in speculative situations.
   Dealers expressed some disappointment that Wall Street wasn't
able to build on gains established Tuesday. By the close of the
London session, the Dow Jones Industrial Average was off 10.49
points at 2149.36.
