<HEAD>Pitney Bowes Reports 18 Percent Earnings Increase</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STAMFORD, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pitney Bowes Inc. said Wednesday that net
income for the third quarter rose 18 percent and attributed the
gain to strong performances in its mailing, shipping, copying,
voice processing and facsimile businesses.
   The Stamford-based company said this year's third-quarter income
of $54 million, or 68 cents per share, compared to $46 million, or
58 cents per share, in the same period last year.
   Last year's third-quarter income included $984,000 from
discontinued operations, the company said.
   Revenue in the quarter ended Sept. 30 rose to $571.9 million
compared with $505.3 million in the third quarter of 1987.
   Net income for the first nine months of 1988 increased 25
percent to $164.5 million, or $2.09 per share, from $131.5 million,
or $1.66 per share in 1987.
   Revenue for the first nine months of 1988 increased 14 percent
to $1.7 billion from $1.5 billion.
